Package common.dataClasses

Class Order

java.lang.Object
common.dataClasses.Order
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Order
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
Represents an order placed by an organisation. IDEALLY, THIS CLASS IS READ ONLY (ONLY GETTERS, NO SETTERS) AS IT IS NEVER MODIFIED BY THE CLIENT.

  • Constructor Details

    • Order

      public Order​(int orderId, java.lang.String orderType, CartItem cartItem, Organisation organisation, int resolvedQuantity, java.time.LocalDateTime orderDateTime, java.time.LocalDateTime finishedDateTime, java.lang.String status)
      Initiates an Order object.
      Parameters:
      orderId - The ID of the order.
      orderType - The type of the order (sell / buy).
      cartItem - The item associated with the order (contains name, quantity & price).
      organisation - The organisation which placed the order (contains ID, name & balance)
      resolvedQuantity - The quantity which the order has been resolved.
      orderDateTime - The date and time when the order was placed.
      finishedDateTime - The date and time when the order was finished.
      status - The status of the order (pending, finished, cancelled)
